subsection.p:
Now integrate around the unit circle C:\quad \mathbf r(t)=(\cos t,\sin t), \qquad 0\le t\le2\pi. Along this circle, x=\cos t,\qquad y=\sin t, so dx=-\sin t\,dt, \qquad dy=\cos t\,dt. Then
\alpha \amp= \frac{-(\sin t)(-\sin t\,dt)+(\cos t)(\cos t\,dt)}{\cos^2t+\sin^2t} \amp= dt.
Therefore \boxed{\oint_C \alpha=2\pi.}

